# REDIRECTOR

Redirector is a backend url shortener-style project.
Supports user authentication, url creation, and url analytics.
Project is built in Node.js and Express, used Prisma with Neon for database.

## NOTES
- Make sure .env is setup properly.
- I set up PORT to be 5000/5001 but it can be changed to any PORT by changing inside .env or server.js.
- When creating a url if a user is logged-in url will not expire and have analytics, otherwise url expires in 7 days and no analytics.
- Users can only access url analytics they own.

## Tech Stack
- Node.js
- Express.js
- Prisma
- Prisma Client
- dotenv
- nodemon
- axios
- bcryptjs
- cookie-parser
- crypto
- zod

## Features
- User authentication with JWT
- Create users
- Click table within Url table
- Url table within User table
- Secure routes with ownership checks
- Url access counter
- Url access information like ip, userAgent, country, and referer
- Unique code generation
- Ip rate limited to create 5 urls per minute


## API Endpoints

AUTH ROUTES
METHOD       ROUTES                     DESCRIPTION
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST         /auth/register             Registers a user.
POST         /auth/login                Logs in a user.
POST         /auth/logout               Logs out a user. (Client-side logout (JWT token removal))

URL ROUTES
METHOD       ROUTES                     DESCRIPTION
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST         /url/create                Creates a url.
GET          /url/:code                 Access a url with code.

ANALYTICS ROUTES
METHOD       ROUTES                     DESCRIPTION
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET          /analytics/:code           Gets analytics from code.


## Project Setup

- Clone the repository
    git clone https://github.com/danielmiguel02/Redirector.git
    cd Redirector

- Install Dependencies
    npm i

- Environment Variables
    Create a .env file in the root of the project and add the required credentials:
    DATABASE_URL="" // Inside Neon you will be able to grab the url.
    PORT=9000 // Or change it to what you would like to be the PORT.
    NODE_ENV="development"
    JWT_SECRET="" // node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
    JWT_EXPIRES_IN="7d"

- Running the project
    npm run dev

- Authorization
    Authorization: Bearer <your_token_here>


## POST Example

AUTH REGISTER (http://localhost:5000/auth/register)
{
    "name": "Josh",
    "email": "emailtoregister@gmail.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

AUTH LOGIN (http://localhost:5000/auth/login)
{
    "email": "emailtoregister@gmail.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

URL CREATE (http://localhost:5000/url/create)
{
    "url": "https://www.youtube.com"
}

